Okay, so in my BSD code I have:<p><pre><code>  {
    char name[NAME_LEN];
</code></pre>
The people who maintain a GPL&#x27;ed fork notice the problem and make it:<p><pre><code>  {
    char name[NAME_LEN+1];
</code></pre>
So now, I can&#x27;t do that in my BSD code because it&#x27;s copyright infringement? (Unless I make the thing GPL?)<p>Given the insanity of copyright laws, I probably can&#x27;t.
